# Base URL of the Rust API. Server-side only — the browser needs no API config at all, because
# every call to the API is made from the SvelteKit server. Nothing here belongs in PUBLIC_*.
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Must match the API's SESSION_TTL_SECS (crates/api/src/config.rs, default 30 days). This only sets
# the cookie's max-age; the sessions row in Postgres is the authority. Duplicated across two
# codebases, so it is a drift risk — change both.
SESSION_TTL_SECS=2592000

# Abort an API call that hangs, so a stuck API cannot hang server-side rendering.
API_TIMEOUT_MS=10000

# The ceiling on one /ask/stream request — headers AND body. Deliberately not API_TIMEOUT_MS: the API
# runs a query rewrite (an LLM call) and retrieval (an embedding call) BEFORE the first byte, so a
# 10s budget would kill healthy asks.
#
# This is a BACKSTOP and must stay ABOVE the API's own STREAM_DEADLINE (300s, handlers.rs). When the
# API's ceiling fires it ends the stream gracefully and keeps the partial answer; if this one fired
# first it would abort the fetch and lose both the answer and the recorded turn. Raising
# STREAM_DEADLINE without raising this reintroduces exactly that.
ASK_TIMEOUT_MS=330000

# The API URL printed into the widget embed snippet — the address a TENANT'S VISITORS' browsers must
# reach, which is not necessarily API_BASE_URL (that may be internal, e.g. http://api:3000).
# Defaults to API_BASE_URL. Still not PUBLIC_*: this is text we render, not config the browser uses.
# WIDGET_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# REQUIRED IN PRODUCTION. Unset in dev (vite dev knows its own origin).
#
# adapter-node derives the request's origin from the connection, so behind a TLS-terminating proxy
# the app sees plain HTTP while the browser sends `Origin: https://...`. That mismatch fails
# SvelteKit's CSRF check AND both hand-rolled Origin guards, so EVERY form post, upload and
# playground question returns 403 — an app that looks deployed and cannot be used.
#
# The server now refuses to start without this (see src/lib/server/env.ts), rather than letting you
# discover it from user reports.
#
# ORIGIN=https://app.example.com
#
# Alternative, if you would rather trust your proxy's forwarding headers. Set BOTH or neither.
# PROTOCOL_HEADER=x-forwarded-proto
# HOST_HEADER=x-forwarded-host

# Where adapter-node listens. Defaults to 3000.
# PORT=3000
